race.comment: THE HASS (2) is going better than his form suggests and will appreciate the easier assignment. Reunites with Sit who claims 3kgs. Has run well here in the past and is drawn favourably. Gets his chance to break a long run of outs. SHUTTLE RUN (1) failed to bring up the hat-trick here last time but was tackling tougher opposition. This is easier and he has proven versatile with his speed. Drops back to a winning trip and is an obvious danger. OK GERRY (10) was much better here second-up when chasing gamely into the placings. Is open to further improvement and is among the chances. LUCKY DOG (6) was doing his best work late last time at Clare. Drops back to a preferred trip off 38 days and can add some juice to the exotics. Don't overlook.
